  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Sierra Leone Ebola Outbreak Mitigation</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The purpose of the intervention is to raise awareness of the Ebola virus and its modes of transmission, and to reduce the rate of infection and related morbidity and mortality among the general population. The response is focused on prevention with most activities designed to support the Communication Pillar: 
ERFS in Freetown and Tonkolili: Print and disseminate Education &amp;amp; Communication (IEC) materials to promote public awareness; Radio and TV messaging; Establish additional hand washing facilities; Support to DHMT and DMOs (Health structures) e.g. logistics for awareness raising campaigns and training of health staff and relevant stakeholders on Ebola prevention/signs. 
START in Freetown: train health workers on case management; awareness raising through IEC materials, hose to house sensitization and radio messaging; provision of hygiene kits to PHUs.</narrative>
  </description>
